Set or unset environment variables from an "env" or dotenv file.

This package provides two interactive functions:

@enumerate
@item
@samp{envars-set-file}: Set all the environment variables defined in an env
file.
@item
@samp{envars-unset-file}: Unset all the environment variables defined in an env
file.
@end enumerate

When used interactively, each function prompts for a file. By default, the
prompt begins at @samp{envars-dir}.
@end ifnottex

