@node Usage
@chapter Usage

Start by creating an env file in @samp{envars-dir} (by default, @samp{~/.env/}). For
example, create this file in @samp{~/.env/foo}:

@example
FOO=~/foo
BAR=$FOO/bar
ОФИС=ДОМ
BAZ=nosubst:FOO$BAR
@end example

Now, you can run:

@itemize
@item
@samp{M-x envars-set-file}, which will prompt you for a file. All the environment
variables defined in the file will be @strong{set}.
@item
@samp{M-x envars-unset-file}, which will prompt you for a file. All the
environment variables defined in the file will be @strong{unset}.
@end itemize

